Preconditions:
- The input matrix `grid` is not null.
- The input matrix `grid` has at least one row and one column.
- The input matrix `grid` is a binary matrix, meaning it only contains the values 0 and 1.
- The input matrix `grid` is a square matrix, meaning it has the same number of rows and columns.
- The value of the cell at position (0, 0) is 1.
- The value of the cell at position (m - 1, n - 1) is 1.

Postconditions:
- The method returns a boolean value indicating whether it is possible to make the matrix disconnect by flipping at most one cell.
- If it is possible to make the matrix disconnect, the method returns true.
- If it is not possible to make the matrix disconnect, the method returns false.